1
00:00:03,666 --> 00:00:06,000
- We didn't go through all
of this just to stop now!

2
00:00:06,083 --> 00:00:07,666
Is there no other way
to save him?

3
00:00:07,750 --> 00:00:09,250
- That's all, I suppose.

4
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:11,625
You can do as you like
with him now.

5
00:00:16,916 --> 00:00:18,083
<i>- I swear.</i>

6
00:00:19,291 --> 00:00:20,875
<i>I'll save you.</i>

7
00:00:20,958 --> 00:00:22,416
- [groans]

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,416
Another unfamiliar ceiling.

9
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:30,375
[grunting]

10
00:00:30,458 --> 00:00:32,208
[gasps]

11
00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:34,833
[groans]

12
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:38,458
So they managed to save
my life but just barely,

13
00:00:38,541 --> 00:00:40,125
and these are the scars.

14
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:43,333
[exhales]

15
00:00:48,208 --> 00:00:49,708
Emilia.

16
00:00:50,666 --> 00:00:54,875
I suppose now I owe her yet
another debt for rescuing me.

17
00:00:54,958 --> 00:00:56,916
- I don't know about that.
- [grunts]

18
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,625
- 'Cause this time you
produced results equal

19
00:00:59,708 --> 00:01:01,125
to the effort you invested.

20
00:01:01,208 --> 00:01:03,000
So I seriously doubt Lia
will think of it

21
00:01:03,083 --> 00:01:04,666
as some kind of debt.

22
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:05,791
- Hey, Puck.

23
00:01:05,875 --> 00:01:07,375
- Hey, good morning, Subaru.

24
00:01:07,458 --> 00:01:09,916
- You say that these are results
equal to my effort

25
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,958
but I don't really remember
much of anything

26
00:01:12,041 --> 00:01:14,500
after I got nommed on
by those dogs in the forest.

27
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:17,125
- "Nommed on?"
That's a cute way to put it.

28
00:01:17,208 --> 00:01:18,916
But it was actually more like,

29
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,291
munch, garble, scarf, chew,
chop, snap, crack, roar!

30
00:01:22,375 --> 00:01:24,208
Well, at least
for the most part.

31
00:01:24,291 --> 00:01:26,333
- With all those viscous
sound effects,

32
00:01:26,416 --> 00:01:28,208
I should definitely
be dead right now.

33
00:01:28,291 --> 00:01:30,500
I think I'm five or six
arms short for all that.

34
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:32,333
- Yeah, you were lucky
you didn't go alone,

35
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:33,625
that's for sure.

36
00:01:33,708 --> 00:01:35,416
The blue-haired maid took
the rest of the damage.

37
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,458
- [groans]
- And she was in awful shape.

38
00:01:37,541 --> 00:01:40,416
Though she heals fast thanks
to her demon transformation.

39
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,416
By the time she carried you back
to the village,

40
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:44,291
she had no visible injuries
at all.

41
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,666
- [groans]
Come on.

42
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,250
Don't scare me like that.

43
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:51,083
Anyway, so Rem went back
to the village, then?

44
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:52,791
Hey, wait!
The kids!

45
00:01:52,875 --> 00:01:54,708
Do you know
if the curse was removed?

46
00:01:54,791 --> 00:01:56,208
- No need to worry.

47
00:01:56,291 --> 00:01:59,000
Betty and I took care of it
so everything's fine.

48
00:01:59,083 --> 00:02:00,083
Way to go.

49
00:02:00,166 --> 00:02:01,541
Your judgment was right
on the mark.

50
00:02:01,625 --> 00:02:03,375
Applause, applause.
Clap, clap.

51
00:02:03,458 --> 00:02:05,875
- [exhales]
Has Emilia been here all night?

52
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,291
- Yeah.

53
00:02:07,375 --> 00:02:09,375
She totally drained
her resources.

54
00:02:09,458 --> 00:02:12,375
She used everything right down
to her od to heal you.

55
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:14,166
You should let her sleep.

56
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:21,375
<i>[Konomi Suzuki's "Redo"]</i>

57
00:02:21,458 --> 00:02:28,375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

58
00:02:28,458 --> 00:02:31,375
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

59
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:38,500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

60
00:03:03,958 --> 00:03:11,000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

61
00:03:33,458 --> 00:03:40,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

62
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:52,375
[birds chirping]

63
00:03:54,625 --> 00:03:56,583
- Barusu, you're awake.

64
00:03:56,666 --> 00:03:57,875
- Ram.

65
00:03:57,958 --> 00:04:00,875
Listen, um, I mean,
about Rem, uh--

66
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:03,166
[stomach growls]
[groans]

67
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:04,750
- How pitifully shameful
you are,

68
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:06,791
pestering other people
for food so soon

69
00:04:06,875 --> 00:04:08,833
after being that badly injured.
- [grunts]

70
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:10,750
- Maybe those dog bites
rubbed off on you.

71
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:13,500
- How the heck do dog bites
rub off on someone?

72
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:15,083
- Eat this.
- Hmm?

73
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:19,583
- [shouting]

74
00:04:19,666 --> 00:04:21,125
- Delicious, isn't it?

75
00:04:21,208 --> 00:04:24,166
- I thought I was gonna die!
But yes, it was good!

76
00:04:24,250 --> 00:04:25,625
- It's freshly made.

77
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:28,125
Rather, it's freshly steamed,
I mean.

78
00:04:28,208 --> 00:04:29,958
- Why do you look so proud
of yourself?

79
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:31,666
- Easy, easy.
You're welcome

80
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:34,000
to have another one,
so just be quiet and eat it.

81
00:04:34,083 --> 00:04:35,916
And, well, as for last night,

82
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,625
you have my sincerest gratitude,
Barusu.

83
00:04:38,708 --> 00:04:40,208
Very nice work.

84
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:41,416
- Nice work?

85
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,500
Always with
the condescending tone.

86
00:04:43,583 --> 00:04:45,708
Was it something deserving
of your thanks?

87
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:47,916
Huh?

88
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,083
- When a domain's people
suffer loss,

89
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:51,916
its lord is held liable.

90
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,666
I hate to think what would have
happened if that pack of ulgarm

91
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:56,375
had further endangered
those children.

92
00:04:56,458 --> 00:04:59,208
You were right
to do what you did.

93
00:04:59,291 --> 00:05:00,875
- What's an ulgarm?

94
00:05:00,958 --> 00:05:03,250
Is that what you guys call
those black mabeasts?

95
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:06,000
- Indeed,
but it's all right now.

96
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:08,833
I reconnected the broken barrier

97
00:05:08,916 --> 00:05:10,916
so the village
is no longer in danger.

98
00:05:19,875 --> 00:05:22,000
<i>I kept an eye on it overnight</i>

99
00:05:22,083 --> 00:05:23,708
<i>to ensure there</i>
<i>were no problems.</i>

100
00:05:23,791 --> 00:05:26,166
<i>-Now no ulgarm should be able</i>
<i>to cross over</i>

101
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:27,375
<i>and enter the village.</i>

102
00:05:27,458 --> 00:05:29,083
<i>So you can relax.</i>

103
00:05:29,166 --> 00:05:32,125
<i>[uplifting music]</i>

104
00:05:32,208 --> 00:05:35,958
<i>♪ ♪</i>

105
00:05:36,041 --> 00:05:38,208
- Ah.
[grunts]

106
00:05:39,291 --> 00:05:40,666
Beako.

107
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:42,708
Hey, I heard you played
a big part

108
00:05:42,791 --> 00:05:44,416
in removing the curse
from those kids.

109
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:46,541
Thanks so much for that.
- No big deal.

110
00:05:46,625 --> 00:05:48,916
The only reason Betty helped
at all was because

111
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,500
Bubby asked,
I suppose.

112
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:53,208
I have something more important
to discuss.

113
00:05:53,291 --> 00:05:54,666
- Huh?

114
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:57,791
[birds chirping]

115
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:01,916
What's so important that you had
to drag me all the way out here

116
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,208
to talk about it, anyway?

117
00:06:05,458 --> 00:06:07,708
- In just a little less
than half a day,

118
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:09,583
you'll almost certainly die,
I suppose.

119
00:06:09,666 --> 00:06:13,208
- [grunting]

120
00:06:13,291 --> 00:06:16,625
- You don't look anywhere near
as disturbed as I was expecting.

121
00:06:16,708 --> 00:06:19,000
I thought you'd scream
and cry, I suppose.

122
00:06:19,083 --> 00:06:22,458
- The curse still isn't lifted,
then, is it?

123
00:06:22,541 --> 00:06:25,166
- When the pack of mabeasts
attacked you in the forest,

124
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:28,250
they planted even more of them
deep inside you.

125
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:29,958
- Gotcha.
Can I ask why this one

126
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:31,916
can't be removed?
One, or more than one?

127
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:34,291
- There's a simple enough
explanation, I suppose.

128
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:36,791
So many curses have been
stacked up inside you,

129
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:39,166
the removal would be
too complex.

130
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:40,500
- What do you mean?

131
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:42,916
- When there's only one curse
to contend with,

132
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,500
removing it is as simple
as untying a knot.

133
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:47,958
But after the bites
from that mabeast attack,

134
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:50,833
the curses on you are
a complex web of many threads

135
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:52,625
far too tangled to undo.

136
00:06:52,708 --> 00:06:55,166
- I get the idea that it's high
on the difficulty scale,

137
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:56,791
but why only half a day?

138
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:58,250
- Because after that,

139
00:06:58,333 --> 00:07:00,750
mabeasts activate their spells
to replenish mana.

140
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:02,000
- [gasps]

141
00:07:02,083 --> 00:07:04,375
- The curse that they used
on you effectively

142
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:06,833
drains a target's mana,
I suppose.

143
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:10,041
Basically, they've turned you
into a heaping pile

144
00:07:10,125 --> 00:07:11,458
of mabeast food.

145
00:07:12,208 --> 00:07:14,958
- So they attack people
because they're hungry?

146
00:07:15,041 --> 00:07:18,291
Wild animals for you.
So simple-minded.

147
00:07:18,375 --> 00:07:19,833
I guess we should count
ourselves lucky

148
00:07:19,916 --> 00:07:22,625
that those mangy mutts never
got hungry before now.

149
00:07:22,708 --> 00:07:24,666
- It's so odd.
- Huh?

150
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:26,750
- You aren't scared,
I suppose?

151
00:07:26,833 --> 00:07:29,125
I'm telling you exactly how
much time you have left

152
00:07:29,208 --> 00:07:30,250
to live,
you know.

153
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:32,541
- Well, sure,
of course I'm scared.

154
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:35,000
But I seriously doubt you came
all the way out here just

155
00:07:35,083 --> 00:07:36,833
to tell me I'm gonna die.

156
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:38,875
Honestly, I don't think even you
could be that mean.

157
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,958
- And what makes you
the expert on me

158
00:07:41,041 --> 00:07:42,250
all of a sudden,
I suppose?

159
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:44,041
- Well, if nothing else,

160
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:45,916
I feel like I've known you
four times longer

161
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,250
than I actually have.

162
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:49,291
- You make no sense at all.

163
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:52,375
But it's a fact that the chance
for you to be saved

164
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:53,583
is much lower now.

165
00:07:53,666 --> 00:07:55,000
- Give it to me straight.

166
00:07:55,083 --> 00:07:58,000
Exactly how low are my odds
for surviving here?

167
00:07:58,083 --> 00:08:01,166
- What you're dealing with is
being eaten because of a spell.

168
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:03,375
If the one that's doing
the eating were to die,

169
00:08:03,458 --> 00:08:05,916
logic dictates the meal would
be canceled, I suppose.

170
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,708
- So that's it, huh?

171
00:08:07,791 --> 00:08:09,750
I just have to take down
every last one

172
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:11,708
of the things that cursed me.

173
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:13,291
[grunts]

174
00:08:13,375 --> 00:08:16,208
But every last one of them
is way too many.

175
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:17,666
- Correct.

176
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:20,208
That's the reason why Bubby
hasn't told that silly girl

177
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:21,500
about the curse.

178
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:22,916
- If Emilia knew,

179
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,666
she'd definitely try to do more
than she's capable of.

180
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:28,500
Which makes me really happy
but also feel really scared

181
00:08:28,583 --> 00:08:30,000
at the same time.

182
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:32,333
Difficulty level here
is seriously demonic.

183
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:33,750
This is impossible.

184
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:35,291
I might as well give up.

185
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:37,250
<i>- We didn't go through all</i>
<i>of this just to stop now.</i>

186
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:40,083
<i>Is there no other way</i>
<i>to save him?</i>

187
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:41,958
<i>- His head must be hurting,</i>
<i>I suppose.</i>

188
00:08:42,041 --> 00:08:43,791
<i>Guess that's not</i>
<i>terribly surprising.</i>

189
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,791
<i>That's all, I suppose.</i>

190
00:08:47,875 --> 00:08:49,958
<i>You can do as you like</i>
<i>with him now.</i>

191
00:08:51,416 --> 00:08:53,750
<i>- I swear I'll save you.</i>

192
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,458
<i>- It can't be.</i>

193
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:59,458
Where is Rem?

194
00:08:59,958 --> 00:09:01,041
Beako.

195
00:09:01,125 --> 00:09:03,250
Beatrice, tell me.
Where is Rem?

196
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:06,291
If you were in her position,
what would you do, I suppose?

197
00:09:08,041 --> 00:09:10,166
- I'm not going to ignore
what you just said.

198
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,166
- [grunts]
Ram.

199
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:13,458
- Miss Beatrice.

200
00:09:13,541 --> 00:09:16,333
Rem didn't go into
the forest alone, did she?

201
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:19,125
- [panting]

202
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:20,625
<i>I have to.</i>

203
00:09:20,708 --> 00:09:22,416
<i>I have to do this all on my own.</i>

204
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,291
<i>I have to save him.</i>

205
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:27,208
<i>No one else needs</i>
<i>to get hurt.</i>

206
00:09:27,291 --> 00:09:28,500
<i>- But why?</i>

207
00:09:28,583 --> 00:09:30,125
Why in the world would Rem go

208
00:09:30,208 --> 00:09:31,708
to such dangerous lengths
for me?

209
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:33,250
- [grunts]
- Hey!

210
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,875
Hold on!

211
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:36,125
- Let go of me, Barusu!

212
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:38,250
I'm not calm enough
to be kind right now.

213
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:39,541
You need to release me at once!

214
00:09:39,625 --> 00:09:40,958
- If you want to save Rem,

215
00:09:41,041 --> 00:09:42,958
and if you consider me
an ally at all,

216
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:44,375
stop for a second, okay?

217
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,583
Do you know where she is?

218
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,833
- No, but if I use
my clairvoyance, I will.

219
00:09:48,916 --> 00:09:50,208
- Your what?

220
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:52,750
- It's a special power that
allows me to see what all

221
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:55,541
the bugs and animals on my
wavelength are seeing as well.

222
00:09:55,625 --> 00:09:59,416
- So all those eyes act like
your security cameras?

223
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,333
Well, if we can use it
to get to Rem,

224
00:10:01,416 --> 00:10:02,708
then fine.

225
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:04,166
Now let me ask you.

226
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:06,708
Are you the kind
of maid that fights?

227
00:10:06,791 --> 00:10:09,250
- What does a question
like that even mean?

228
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:11,958
- It means I plan on going into
the forest with you.

229
00:10:12,041 --> 00:10:13,833
- You're following me?
- That's right,

230
00:10:13,916 --> 00:10:15,208
'cause when it comes
to fighting,

231
00:10:15,291 --> 00:10:16,416
I'll totally get in your way.

232
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,791
- [gasps]

233
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:20,166
If you expect me to be able
to fight like Rem does

234
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:21,708
in her demon form,
I can't.

235
00:10:21,791 --> 00:10:23,666
- Wait a second.
You're twins, right?

236
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:24,958
If Rem is a demon,

237
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,708
wouldn't that make you
a demon, too?

238
00:10:26,791 --> 00:10:28,333
- [gasps]

239
00:10:29,541 --> 00:10:31,083
In a way,
I suppose that's true,

240
00:10:31,166 --> 00:10:33,291
but unlike Rem,
I'm hornless.

241
00:10:33,375 --> 00:10:34,458
- [grunts]

242
00:10:34,541 --> 00:10:35,833
- [gasps]

243
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:38,541
I can only use a rather extreme
bit of wind magic.

244
00:10:38,625 --> 00:10:40,250
[grunts]

245
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:41,833
[whooshing]

246
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:43,708
- Going to retrieve
the younger sister

247
00:10:43,791 --> 00:10:45,958
from the dangers of the forest
would mean giving up

248
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:47,291
on your own life.

249
00:10:47,375 --> 00:10:49,458
You do understand that fact,
I suppose.

250
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:51,708
- [chuckles]
Well, that's not quite right.

251
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:53,291
Let me correct you.

252
00:10:53,375 --> 00:10:56,458
It's dumb to just start giving
up 'cause you're used to dying.

253
00:10:56,541 --> 00:10:58,958
You get one life so you
should make the best of it.

254
00:10:59,041 --> 00:11:01,166
That's something I realized
after you guys went through

255
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:02,708
so much to save mine.

256
00:11:02,791 --> 00:11:05,875
So if you don't mind,
I'm gonna struggle pathetically.

257
00:11:05,958 --> 00:11:08,583
Let's go out there
and make a comeback!

258
00:11:08,666 --> 00:11:11,958
I've recovered from the terrible
state I was in earlier.

259
00:11:12,041 --> 00:11:14,208
I guess you could say
I'm a greedy guy

260
00:11:14,291 --> 00:11:16,750
because I wanna see
the continuation of this story

261
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:18,166
and with me in it.

262
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:19,625
Now I think it's time
to get moving

263
00:11:19,708 --> 00:11:21,666
to our last big showdown!

264
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:24,833
You hear me, fate?
Bring it on!

265
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,125
[rain pattering]

266
00:11:29,208 --> 00:11:30,416
- [grunts]

267
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:31,500
- I must say you gave

268
00:11:31,583 --> 00:11:33,750
a pretty heroic speech
back there.

269
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,916
But when I see you lagging
behind so close

270
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,458
to becoming nothing but baggage,

271
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:39,416
it's difficult to hide
my disappointment.

272
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:41,458
- Give me a break.
I'm still recovering,

273
00:11:41,541 --> 00:11:44,166
so my energy's spent
and I'm low on blood.

274
00:11:44,541 --> 00:11:46,708
Oh, I didn't get the chance
to hear Mili say,

275
00:11:46,791 --> 00:11:49,000
"I'll see you soon,"
in her sweet little voice.

276
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,583
- Until you say,
"I'm home,"

277
00:11:50,666 --> 00:11:53,291
last night's "see you soon"
is still in effect.

278
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:55,791
- Oh, really?
Is that how it works?

279
00:11:55,875 --> 00:11:58,458
- Besides, didn't you get
something from someone

280
00:11:58,541 --> 00:11:59,791
other than Miss Emilia?

281
00:11:59,875 --> 00:12:01,750
- [grunts]

282
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:02,833
Sure did.

283
00:12:02,916 --> 00:12:04,833
Something pretty beautiful,
in fact.

284
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:07,916
- I want you
to take this.

285
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,875
It's the sharpest sword
in the village.

286
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:11,416
- Thanks, I appreciate it.

287
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,208
- We're counting on you.
- Subaru!

288
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:14,833
- [grunts]
[all laughing]

289
00:12:14,916 --> 00:12:16,458
all: Subaru!
- Hey, guys.

290
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,541
So you're all awake, huh?
- Where are you headed?

291
00:12:18,625 --> 00:12:20,625
- Back into the forest?
- Don't do it.

292
00:12:20,708 --> 00:12:22,875
It's dangerous, Subaru.
- I'll be fine.

293
00:12:22,958 --> 00:12:24,375
Don't worry about a thing.

294
00:12:24,458 --> 00:12:26,875
I'm not gonna go anywhere.
- So what's the sword for?

295
00:12:26,958 --> 00:12:28,166
- You mean this?

296
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,500
- Let's call it a thank you gift
from all of us.

297
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,833
- I wanna thank you, too!
- Hey, easy!

298
00:12:32,916 --> 00:12:35,125
[all laughing]

299
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:37,291
[grunts]

300
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,625
Candy,
a pretty stone.

301
00:12:42,208 --> 00:12:43,958
I wonder what else
is in here.

302
00:12:45,208 --> 00:12:46,916
Ah, it's a big freakin' bug!

303
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,750
Damn brats sneaking that gross
thing in while I was distracted.

304
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,583
I'll give them
a talking-to later.

305
00:12:51,666 --> 00:12:53,250
- It's only proof
of their admiration,

306
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:55,500
though I wonder what they see
in a man like you.

307
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,208
- In the pure eyes of a child,

308
00:12:57,291 --> 00:13:00,666
my true manly nature shines like
a bright star in the night sky.

309
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:01,958
And as I recall,

310
00:13:02,041 --> 00:13:03,500
I'm not the only one
they like, either.

311
00:13:03,583 --> 00:13:05,583
You could tell, right?

312
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:08,416
- Yes, I could.

313
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,500
[all laughing]

314
00:13:09,583 --> 00:13:12,208
- Hey, why did you put dirt
in there?

315
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:14,625
- [grunting]

316
00:13:14,708 --> 00:13:17,375
- Ram-Ram!

317
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:20,041
We wanna thank Rem-Ram properly,
too,

318
00:13:20,125 --> 00:13:22,291
so bring her over later, okay?

319
00:13:22,375 --> 00:13:24,208
Promise, Ram-Ram!

320
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:26,625
- [gasps]

321
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:29,625
[grunts]

322
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:31,750
Barusu, I'm gong to use
my clairvoyance.

323
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,250
Give me a moment, all right?

324
00:13:51,375 --> 00:13:54,208
Barusu, something nearby
is watching us both right now.

325
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:56,333
- What?
- Up there.

326
00:13:56,416 --> 00:13:58,166
- Up where?
[shouts]

327
00:13:58,250 --> 00:14:00,500
[grunts]
- Get ready.

328
00:14:00,583 --> 00:14:02,833
More are coming.
[both grunting]

329
00:14:02,916 --> 00:14:04,250
[snarling]

330
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:07,791
- [screaming]

331
00:14:07,875 --> 00:14:10,458
Hey, wait up!
Don't just walk off!

332
00:14:11,166 --> 00:14:13,416
[grunts]
- Anyway,

333
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,541
why does it seem
like every individual

334
00:14:15,625 --> 00:14:17,000
loses their head
when they see you?

335
00:14:17,083 --> 00:14:19,833
To be perfectly honest,
I don't understand it at all.

336
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:24,416
Is it because you seem
like such a weakling?

337
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,500
- After all that hesitation,
that's your conclusion?

338
00:14:26,583 --> 00:14:27,666
Rude.

339
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:29,083
- Is it because you seem
like a wimp, then?

340
00:14:29,166 --> 00:14:30,750
- You may have reworded things
a bit,

341
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:32,333
but that doesn't change the root

342
00:14:32,416 --> 00:14:34,208
of what you're saying,
Ram-Ram.

343
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:38,666
Hey, would it be okay
if I asked what that

344
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:41,041
hornless thing you
mentioned before means?

345
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:48,166
- It's nothing.

346
00:14:48,625 --> 00:14:50,000
As the term implies,

347
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:53,041
it's another name for a foolish
demon without a horn.

348
00:14:53,875 --> 00:14:56,625
Long ago, after getting into
a little trouble,

349
00:14:56,708 --> 00:14:58,625
I lost the only one I had.

350
00:14:58,708 --> 00:15:00,208
Since that point in time,

351
00:15:00,291 --> 00:15:02,500
I've relied on Rem
for everything.

352
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:06,208
- I suppose I shouldn't have
asked about it then, huh?

353
00:15:06,291 --> 00:15:08,250
- Why's that?
- Well, I'm not gonna pretend

354
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:09,791
like I know anything about
your people

355
00:15:09,875 --> 00:15:12,416
or how important horns are
to the race you call demons,

356
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,583
but I assume it's a pretty
serious problem.

357
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:16,708
So I just figured after asking
about it that it might

358
00:15:16,791 --> 00:15:18,708
have been a little insensitive
of me.

359
00:15:20,083 --> 00:15:21,458
- Back then was one matter.

360
00:15:21,541 --> 00:15:23,333
But now things have calmed down.

361
00:15:23,416 --> 00:15:25,500
There are things I've gained
and lives I've saved

362
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:26,708
by losing my horn.

363
00:15:26,791 --> 00:15:28,416
I'm sure Rem doesn't feel

364
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:30,250
the same way I do about it,
though.

365
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:31,625
- Huh?

366
00:15:32,291 --> 00:15:35,375
- Originally, members
of the demon race had two horns

367
00:15:35,458 --> 00:15:36,708
but when twins are born,

368
00:15:36,791 --> 00:15:39,583
the pairs split with each child
having only one.

369
00:15:39,666 --> 00:15:41,000
- [snarls]

370
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:42,666
<i>- So twins are detested,</i>

371
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:46,500
<i>and it's customary to dispose</i>
<i>of them immediately after birth.</i>

372
00:15:46,583 --> 00:15:48,833
<i>But Rem and I were allowed</i>
<i>to live.</i>

373
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:51,583
<i>A demon's horns awaken</i>
<i>its demon instincts</i>

374
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:53,250
<i>and allow it to devour mana,</i>

375
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:55,666
<i>significantly heightening</i>
<i>its ferocity</i>

376
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:58,791
<i>and combat ability,</i>
<i>but if one is reckless,</i>

377
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:00,791
<i>the recoil will leave</i>
<i>them battered.</i>

378
00:16:00,875 --> 00:16:03,791
- [shouting]

379
00:16:03,875 --> 00:16:07,083
[dogs barking]

380
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:09,333
<i>- I don't wanna see Rem</i>
<i>like that.</i>

381
00:16:10,125 --> 00:16:12,125
- Are you feeling worried
because you care for her?

382
00:16:12,208 --> 00:16:13,500
- Well, yes, of course.

383
00:16:13,583 --> 00:16:16,708
It's true that she's
much stronger than I am

384
00:16:16,791 --> 00:16:19,375
but that doesn't mean I'm not
concerned for her safety.

385
00:16:20,666 --> 00:16:21,833
- [grunts]

386
00:16:21,916 --> 00:16:23,208
- No matter what we're told
to do,

387
00:16:23,291 --> 00:16:25,083
she always does it far better.

388
00:16:25,166 --> 00:16:27,625
But in the end,
I'm still her older sister.

389
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,125
And I'm not ever wavering
from that position.

390
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:31,708
- [grunts]

391
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:33,708
Is that so?

392
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:36,000
Okay, I think I understand.

393
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,833
And I've got an idea now.

394
00:16:37,916 --> 00:16:39,875
So don't worry.
We'll bring Rem back safe.

395
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:41,333
- [grunts[

396
00:16:42,083 --> 00:16:45,041
<i>- If my idea's right,</i>
<i>they're sure to come.</i>

397
00:16:45,125 --> 00:16:47,083
<i>They'll be drawn here</i>
<i>by my attempt to tell her</i>

398
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:48,708
<i>about Return by Death.</i>

399
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:51,000
Listen, Ram,
the thing is,

400
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:52,166
I can Return by--

401
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:54,083
[birds squawking]

402
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:55,791
- What's that?

403
00:16:55,875 --> 00:16:57,000
- [gasping]

404
00:16:57,083 --> 00:16:59,000
I made a wager that seems
to have paid off,

405
00:16:59,083 --> 00:17:00,875
but it brought a bit
of pain with it, too.

406
00:17:00,958 --> 00:17:02,750
- What did you do, Barusu?

407
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:05,333
The wind is erratic
and I smell beasts approaching.

408
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:07,083
A large number of them.

409
00:17:07,166 --> 00:17:09,083
And on top of that,
we haven't found Rem yet.

410
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:10,750
- Well, don't worry about that.

411
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:13,583
I feel like our paths will cross
with hers pretty soon.

412
00:17:13,666 --> 00:17:15,250
- What makes you so sure?

413
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:18,375
- Because I've been covered
in the Witch's scent.

414
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:19,708
- [gasps]

415
00:17:19,791 --> 00:17:22,250
- Rem's goal is to hunt down
all the mabeasts, right?

416
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,500
They'll all be drawn
to the sudden increase

417
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:25,708
in the Witch's scent

418
00:17:25,791 --> 00:17:27,125
and make their way straight
for me.

419
00:17:27,208 --> 00:17:28,791
Then Rem will have no choice

420
00:17:28,875 --> 00:17:30,791
but to follow those hell hounds
toward us.

421
00:17:30,875 --> 00:17:34,750
It's a plan I call Operation:
Subaru Natsuki is the Bait.

422
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:37,750
[dogs snarling]

423
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:40,125
Okay, I'm gonna have to rely
on you to do most

424
00:17:40,208 --> 00:17:42,125
of the fighting so feel free
to go for it.

425
00:17:42,208 --> 00:17:43,416
- When this is over,

426
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:45,458
take an objective look
at what you just said

427
00:17:45,541 --> 00:17:47,250
until you wish you were dead!

428
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:57,208
- [gasps]

429
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:58,916
- [grunting]

430
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,458
- This is what I get
for believing you

431
00:18:00,541 --> 00:18:02,125
when you said you could fight!

432
00:18:02,208 --> 00:18:04,625
- Well, I was fighting,
wasn't I?

433
00:18:04,708 --> 00:18:07,666
The problem was my strength
didn't hold out as long

434
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:11,416
as I thought it would.
- Damn it!

435
00:18:12,125 --> 00:18:13,708
Crap!
[shouts]

436
00:18:13,791 --> 00:18:17,541
[screaming]

437
00:18:17,625 --> 00:18:21,416
Damn it all!

438
00:18:24,416 --> 00:18:26,125
Oh, that was close!

439
00:18:26,208 --> 00:18:28,333
We were almost dead meat.

440
00:18:28,416 --> 00:18:29,958
- If we fall from this height,

441
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:31,500
we'll both be in trouble.

442
00:18:31,583 --> 00:18:33,375
Barusu, can you climb up?

443
00:18:33,458 --> 00:18:35,833
- I'd like to make it up
by sheer will power,

444
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:38,333
but the mabeasts waiting
up there are kind of a problem.

445
00:18:38,416 --> 00:18:42,583
Ah, the sharpest sword!

446
00:18:42,666 --> 00:18:44,000
- El Fula!

447
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:45,416
- [shouts]

448
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:49,041
[grunting]

449
00:18:49,125 --> 00:18:50,500
Man, that was close.

450
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:54,166
Seriously, Ram had timing
like Buddha.

451
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:56,375
Hold on.
Hey, Ram.

452
00:18:56,458 --> 00:18:58,333
Hey!

453
00:18:58,416 --> 00:19:00,375
You can't be serious.

454
00:19:00,458 --> 00:19:01,791
Damn it all!

455
00:19:01,875 --> 00:19:03,125
[dogs snarling]

456
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:04,750
[gasping]

457
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:07,208
[snarling continues]

458
00:19:07,291 --> 00:19:09,875
Holy shit, the timing
of all this couldn't possibly

459
00:19:09,958 --> 00:19:12,666
be any worse.
[groans]

460
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:17,208
[grunts]

461
00:19:17,291 --> 00:19:19,291
Rem!

462
00:19:20,625 --> 00:19:23,208
- [chuckles]
- Thank goodness you're alive!

463
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:25,083
We're finally saved/

464
00:19:29,083 --> 00:19:31,125
[shouts]

465
00:19:31,208 --> 00:19:33,541
<i>[tense music]</i>

466
00:19:33,625 --> 00:19:35,833
You're kidding me!
She can turn into a demon,

467
00:19:35,916 --> 00:19:37,166
but she can't control it?

468
00:19:39,583 --> 00:19:40,875
- [snarls]

469
00:19:40,958 --> 00:19:41,916
- Hey, Rem!

470
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,416
My name is Subaru Natsuki,

471
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:45,125
a useless trainee
in various odd jobs

472
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:46,666
though I always try my best!

473
00:19:46,750 --> 00:19:48,750
The Roswaal Mansion's most
promising servant!

474
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:50,250
I've caused trouble
for you and Ram

475
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:51,916
but we've been friends at times
and we've fought at times.

476
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,250
[grunts]

477
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:56,250
Trying to beat me to death while
I'm still talking to you

478
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:57,833
is bad manners!

479
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,041
- [grunts]

480
00:20:01,125 --> 00:20:02,166
- [whimpers]

481
00:20:04,083 --> 00:20:08,500
[snarling]
[blows landing]

482
00:20:08,583 --> 00:20:10,000
- [grunts]

483
00:20:11,458 --> 00:20:13,708
Now's my chance.

484
00:20:13,791 --> 00:20:15,500
[snarls]

485
00:20:17,625 --> 00:20:18,958
- [gasps]

486
00:20:20,958 --> 00:20:24,208
[screaming]

487
00:20:25,666 --> 00:20:27,750
[grunts]

488
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,125
- Damn, it's no use.

489
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:30,125
I can't ignore her!

490
00:20:30,208 --> 00:20:31,875
Take the plunge, Subaru.

491
00:20:31,958 --> 00:20:35,125
Men are about guts, remember?
Time to prove it!

492
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:36,416
So...

493
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,208
[inhales]

494
00:20:38,291 --> 00:20:40,708
Quit making that face
and try to smile, Rem!

495
00:20:40,791 --> 00:20:42,000
I can Return by--

496
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:48,458
- [shouting]

497
00:20:48,541 --> 00:20:50,458
- [grunts]

498
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:54,833
- [shouting]

499
00:20:54,916 --> 00:20:57,958
- [panting]

500
00:20:58,041 --> 00:20:59,583
- Her horn.
- You're awake?

501
00:20:59,666 --> 00:21:01,666
- I thought this would be
the perfect time

502
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:03,000
for me to wake up.

503
00:21:03,083 --> 00:21:05,375
- You've got good intuition,
Ram.

504
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:06,916
What about her horn?

505
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,041
- That's responsible
for making Rem a demon.

506
00:21:10,125 --> 00:21:12,541
One good solid hit should bring
her back to normal.

507
00:21:12,625 --> 00:21:14,583
- [grunting]
- You sure?

508
00:21:14,666 --> 00:21:16,208
- I am.
I think.

509
00:21:16,291 --> 00:21:17,666
I hope.

510
00:21:17,750 --> 00:21:19,500
- That's kinda vague.

511
00:21:19,583 --> 00:21:21,458
- [grunts]

512
00:21:22,375 --> 00:21:25,708
- A hit to that one little spot?
Doesn't that seem impossible?

513
00:21:25,791 --> 00:21:28,333
- Muster up all your courage
and do something.

514
00:21:28,416 --> 00:21:30,458
- Believe it or not,
I actually do have an idea

515
00:21:30,541 --> 00:21:32,166
for something that we could try
to pull off,

516
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:34,750
but I'm afraid
you're gonna get mad.

517
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:37,166
- Well, if you think that it'll
bring my sister back

518
00:21:37,250 --> 00:21:39,083
to her senses,
then I won't.

519
00:21:39,166 --> 00:21:41,500
- Really?
- Yes, absolutely.

520
00:21:41,583 --> 00:21:43,750
- Do you swear to Ros?

521
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:47,583
- That's the most reckless name
you could have chosen.

522
00:21:47,666 --> 00:21:50,708
But yes,
I swear to Lord Roswaal.

523
00:21:50,791 --> 00:21:52,875
- [laughs]
All right, then!

524
00:21:52,958 --> 00:21:57,041
Heave, ho!

525
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:01,416
- [gasps]

526
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,333
- [grunts]

527
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:08,375
- [grunts]

528
00:22:08,458 --> 00:22:09,708
<i>I freaked out!</i>

529
00:22:09,791 --> 00:22:12,083
<i>I didn't have the guts</i>
<i>to take that last step!</i>

530
00:22:14,541 --> 00:22:16,000
[shouts]

531
00:22:34,583 --> 00:22:37,791
<i>If I let this chance go by,</i>
<i>there won't be any others!</i>

532
00:22:38,583 --> 00:22:41,166
<i>Smile for me, Rem!</i>

533
00:22:41,666 --> 00:22:48,291
<i>Today I'm more demonically</i>
<i>inspired than a real demon!</i>

534
00:22:58,375 --> 00:23:00,916
[distant wolves howling]

535
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,291
- To us of the demon clan,

536
00:23:03,375 --> 00:23:05,875
twins are taboo.

537
00:23:06,458 --> 00:23:08,250
- Please, wait, chief.
I beg of you!

538
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:10,458
- Enough!
To protect our pride as a race,

539
00:23:10,541 --> 00:23:12,458
and to ensure
its continued purity,

540
00:23:12,541 --> 00:23:14,458
we must dispose of them.

541
00:23:14,541 --> 00:23:16,916
Such is the demon clan's custom.

542
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,041
It is our law.

543
00:23:19,125 --> 00:23:22,041
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

544
00:23:22,125 --> 00:23:27,500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

545
00:23:27,583 --> 00:23:31,250
- [crying]

546
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:33,791
[booming]

547
00:23:33,875 --> 00:23:38,291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

548
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:41,458
[all gasping]

549
00:23:41,541 --> 00:23:43,291
[booming]

550
00:23:43,375 --> 00:23:45,500
- [grunts]

551
00:23:45,583 --> 00:23:46,791
[gasps]

552
00:23:48,250 --> 00:23:50,416
One of the children is--

553
00:23:53,291 --> 00:23:55,500
[birds chirping]

554
00:23:59,916 --> 00:24:02,833
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

555
00:24:02,916 --> 00:24:08,833
<i>♪ ♪</i>

556
00:24:08,916 --> 00:24:12,708
[all gasping]

557
00:24:14,625 --> 00:24:17,500
She is a true prodigy.

558
00:24:17,583 --> 00:24:19,791
- Such power with only one horn.

559
00:24:19,875 --> 00:24:23,250
Imagine what she could do
if she'd been born with two.

560
00:24:25,916 --> 00:24:27,625
- That was very good, Ram.

561
00:24:27,708 --> 00:24:29,791
- Rem, you'll have to follow
your sister's example

562
00:24:29,875 --> 00:24:31,916
and work hard.
- Oh, don't you worry.

563
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,125
One day soon Rem will show us
that she has incredible power.

564
00:24:35,208 --> 00:24:36,541
- I've no doubt.

565
00:24:36,625 --> 00:24:38,916
She's Ram's sister so I'm sure
it'll come with time.

566
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,458
- 'Course it will.

567
00:24:40,541 --> 00:24:42,208
- [whimpers]

568
00:24:58,833 --> 00:25:00,416
[gasps]

569
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:02,666
- Don't worry.
- [gasps]

570
00:25:03,791 --> 00:25:06,875
Sissy, I--
- Just be yourself, Rem.

571
00:25:06,958 --> 00:25:08,916
There's no reason for you
to worry about

572
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:10,333
what other people see.

573
00:25:10,416 --> 00:25:17,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

574
00:25:30,125 --> 00:25:33,750
- I can never match my sister
in demon power.

575
00:25:33,833 --> 00:25:35,250
Then...

576
00:25:43,041 --> 00:25:45,583
Hey, Mom?
- Ah?

577
00:25:45,666 --> 00:25:47,791
Yes, Rem, dear?
What is it?

578
00:25:47,875 --> 00:25:51,125
- I've decided that I'm
gonna make dinner tomorrow.

579
00:25:53,041 --> 00:25:55,375
- So what are you thinking
about making?

580
00:25:55,458 --> 00:25:58,083
- Maybe a stir fry
with barbaro rabbit meat

581
00:25:58,166 --> 00:26:00,666
and nuts from the trees
in the forest

582
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:02,500
and some steamed tatoes.

583
00:26:02,583 --> 00:26:04,250
- That sounds good.
I'll help you.

584
00:26:04,333 --> 00:26:06,958
- Mm-mmm.
I'll be okay by myself.

585
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,041
Just watch.

586
00:26:14,166 --> 00:26:15,291
[exhales sharply]

587
00:26:16,708 --> 00:26:19,041
Now I just need
a barbaro rabbit.

588
00:26:26,333 --> 00:26:27,500
[grunts]

589
00:26:27,583 --> 00:26:30,083
[gasps]
[distant thunder claps]

590
00:26:30,166 --> 00:26:31,541
[rain pattering]

591
00:26:31,625 --> 00:26:34,416
[breathing heavily]

592
00:26:36,083 --> 00:26:37,583
[booming]
[screams]

593
00:26:37,666 --> 00:26:39,500
[grunts]

594
00:26:39,583 --> 00:26:41,291
[gasping]

595
00:26:42,708 --> 00:26:43,750
[screams]

596
00:26:47,958 --> 00:26:49,125
[gasps]

597
00:26:49,208 --> 00:26:50,666
Sissy!

598
00:26:50,750 --> 00:26:52,416
- [panting]

599
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:53,916
- [gasps]

600
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:58,333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

601
00:26:58,416 --> 00:27:01,333
- I was worried so I'm really
glad you're both all right.

602
00:27:02,208 --> 00:27:03,958
<i>- She said both.</i>

603
00:27:04,041 --> 00:27:06,333
- Listen, don't go into
the forest alone again,

604
00:27:06,416 --> 00:27:07,625
okay, Ram?

605
00:27:07,708 --> 00:27:09,833
- You don't wanna worry
your sister now, do you?

606
00:27:09,916 --> 00:27:11,000
- No.

607
00:27:11,083 --> 00:27:12,500
You're right.
I won't.

608
00:27:13,791 --> 00:27:16,083
- Wait, let's not forget
about this.

609
00:27:16,166 --> 00:27:19,333
The steamed tatoes Rem went
through so much trouble to make

610
00:27:19,416 --> 00:27:21,333
turned out really good.
Just taste them.

611
00:27:21,416 --> 00:27:23,875
And they have just the right
amount of salt, too.

612
00:27:23,958 --> 00:27:25,916
- Yeah, you're right.
They are good.

613
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:28,375
- [laughs]
I had no idea Rem

614
00:27:28,458 --> 00:27:30,500
could make something
so delicious.

615
00:27:35,625 --> 00:27:39,291
[grunting]

616
00:27:40,625 --> 00:27:41,750
[whimpers]

617
00:27:41,833 --> 00:27:44,625
- Okay, that's enough, Rem.
- [gasps]

618
00:27:45,291 --> 00:27:48,583
- In the end I'm really just
glad both of you are all right.

619
00:27:48,666 --> 00:27:51,333
- Yes, we're so glad
you're safe.

620
00:27:51,416 --> 00:27:52,916
- [whimpers]

621
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:56,583
- No, it would have been much
better if it had only been Ram.

622
00:27:56,666 --> 00:27:59,375
- That's right.
You said it.

623
00:28:00,958 --> 00:28:02,250
- Good point.

624
00:28:02,333 --> 00:28:04,083
If only that useless
Rem had died.

625
00:28:04,166 --> 00:28:06,166
- Leaving Ram as our
only surviving daughter.

626
00:28:06,250 --> 00:28:07,291
That would have been best.

627
00:28:07,375 --> 00:28:09,833
- [crying]

628
00:28:10,208 --> 00:28:13,250
[rain pattering]

629
00:28:15,916 --> 00:28:18,416
[crying]

630
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:20,333
[gasps]

631
00:28:20,416 --> 00:28:23,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

632
00:28:23,541 --> 00:28:25,708
[gasps]

633
00:28:28,833 --> 00:28:29,958
[groans]

634
00:28:30,041 --> 00:28:32,583
- You were having a scary dream,
weren't you?

635
00:28:32,666 --> 00:28:33,916
You were moaning.

636
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:35,625
- Sissy.

637
00:28:35,708 --> 00:28:38,625
- It's okay now 'cause
I'm right here with you.

638
00:28:38,708 --> 00:28:41,250
You'll never have to worry
about anything with me around,

639
00:28:41,333 --> 00:28:43,208
all right?
- Right.

640
00:28:43,291 --> 00:28:44,958
Thank you, Sissy.

641
00:28:46,291 --> 00:28:47,541
I love you.

642
00:28:49,666 --> 00:28:51,875
<i>My sister really is amazing.</i>

643
00:28:51,958 --> 00:28:54,125
<i>I can't match her in anything.</i>

644
00:28:54,208 --> 00:28:58,250
<i>In that case, I don't have</i>
<i>to do anything anymore.</i>

645
00:28:58,333 --> 00:29:00,958
<i>I can just be myself</i>
<i>and walk behind her.</i>

646
00:29:04,791 --> 00:29:07,541
[groans]

647
00:29:07,625 --> 00:29:08,916
[grunts]

648
00:29:10,541 --> 00:29:12,791
Sissy?
[distant booming]

649
00:29:12,875 --> 00:29:14,416
[gasping]

650
00:29:14,500 --> 00:29:16,750
[groans]

651
00:29:17,416 --> 00:29:19,833
[fire roaring]
[gasps]

652
00:29:19,916 --> 00:29:21,000
[whimpers]

653
00:29:25,083 --> 00:29:26,250
[gasps]

654
00:29:26,333 --> 00:29:31,541
[crying]

655
00:29:33,833 --> 00:29:37,416
[blows landing]

656
00:29:38,958 --> 00:29:40,833
[gasps]

657
00:29:44,333 --> 00:29:46,291
[slicing]

658
00:29:46,375 --> 00:29:48,208
Careful, Sissy!

659
00:29:48,958 --> 00:29:51,166
- [grunts]

660
00:29:57,750 --> 00:29:59,416
Oh, Rem.

661
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:01,000
I'm so glad you're safe.

662
00:30:01,083 --> 00:30:02,583
- [whimpers]

663
00:30:06,125 --> 00:30:07,875
[blow lands]

664
00:30:11,583 --> 00:30:13,833
- [gasps]

665
00:30:15,416 --> 00:30:16,833
[exhales]

666
00:30:18,083 --> 00:30:19,916
<i>It finally broke off.</i>

667
00:30:22,125 --> 00:30:23,583
<i>Because of me...</i>

668
00:30:24,541 --> 00:30:26,708
<i>My sister's horn was broken.</i>

669
00:30:26,791 --> 00:30:28,750
<i>And she lost her power.</i>

670
00:30:29,375 --> 00:30:30,708
<i>From now on,</i>

671
00:30:30,791 --> 00:30:34,125
<i>I have to learn to do all</i>
<i>the things that Sissy--</i>

672
00:30:34,208 --> 00:30:35,916
<i>that Sister could do.</i>

673
00:30:36,041 --> 00:30:38,416
<i>This is what Sister</i>
<i>would have done.</i>

674
00:30:38,500 --> 00:30:40,333
<i>Sister was even more amazing.</i>

675
00:30:40,416 --> 00:30:42,208
<i>Sister could do even more.</i>

676
00:30:42,291 --> 00:30:45,166
<i>I'm only imitating</i>
<i>what Sister could do.</i>

677
00:30:45,250 --> 00:30:48,250
<i>If I can't even do that</i>
<i>satisfactorily,</i>

678
00:30:48,333 --> 00:30:50,083
<i>then I'm worthless.</i>

679
00:30:50,166 --> 00:30:52,250
- You're doing an excellent job.

680
00:30:52,333 --> 00:30:56,083
<i>- I heard those words back home</i>
<i>so many times.</i>

681
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,000
- Easy.
Don't overdo it.

682
00:30:59,083 --> 00:31:00,750
<i>- Even if I overdo everything,</i>

683
00:31:00,833 --> 00:31:02,250
<i>it will never be enough.</i>

684
00:31:02,916 --> 00:31:05,416
- I don't understand.
Why do you try so hard?

685
00:31:06,166 --> 00:31:07,458
<i>- Why else?</i>

686
00:31:07,541 --> 00:31:10,000
<i>Because nothing I do</i>
<i>will ever measure up.</i>

687
00:31:10,083 --> 00:31:11,916
<i>Why should I go on living?</i>

688
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,500
<i>All of this is my atonement</i>
<i>for what I felt</i>

689
00:31:14,583 --> 00:31:16,500
<i>on that fiery night.-</i>

690
00:31:16,583 --> 00:31:18,958
<i>What else can I do</i>
<i>to make amends?</i>

691
00:31:19,041 --> 00:31:21,916
<i>I'll risk my life to walk</i>
<i>the very same path</i>

692
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:23,666
<i>that Sister would have walked.</i>

693
00:31:23,750 --> 00:31:25,958
<i>The path I took from her.</i>

694
00:31:26,041 --> 00:31:29,125
<i>Because I'm inferior to her</i>
<i>in every way.</i>

695
00:31:29,208 --> 00:31:32,416
<i>I'm nothing more than</i>
<i>a mediocre replacement.</i>

696
00:31:32,500 --> 00:31:34,708
<i>And that's all I'll ever be.</i>

697
00:31:34,791 --> 00:31:35,791
[cracks]

698
00:31:37,333 --> 00:31:38,791
- [grunting]

699
00:31:38,875 --> 00:31:41,041
- Barusu, head to the right
of that broken tree ahead.

700
00:31:41,125 --> 00:31:42,291
You're too slow.

701
00:31:42,375 --> 00:31:44,583
- Don't ask any more of me.
You got that?

702
00:31:44,666 --> 00:31:46,333
I'm running just as fast
as I can here.

703
00:31:46,416 --> 00:31:48,375
- W--what's going on?

704
00:31:48,458 --> 00:31:49,500
Where are we?

705
00:31:49,583 --> 00:31:51,458
- Rem, you're finally awake!

706
00:31:51,875 --> 00:31:53,208
- Oh, thank goodness.

707
00:31:53,291 --> 00:31:55,125
You really are a handful.
You know that?

708
00:31:55,208 --> 00:31:56,125
[snarls]

709
00:31:56,208 --> 00:31:58,208
[grunts]
Fula!

710
00:31:58,291 --> 00:32:01,500
[dog whines]

711
00:32:01,583 --> 00:32:06,666
[both panting]

712
00:32:06,750 --> 00:32:09,041
- Why?
- Why what?

713
00:32:09,125 --> 00:32:11,333
- Why didn't you just mind
your own business

714
00:32:11,416 --> 00:32:12,833
and leave me alone?

715
00:32:13,750 --> 00:32:17,125
You and Sister showing up
makes it all pointless.

716
00:32:17,208 --> 00:32:19,833
I have to do it by myself,
understand?

717
00:32:19,916 --> 00:32:22,250
Nobody else needs
to get hurt anymore.

718
00:32:23,083 --> 00:32:24,583
- It's too late for that now.

719
00:32:24,666 --> 00:32:26,500
Ram and I are already torn
to shreds,

720
00:32:26,583 --> 00:32:27,583
maybe even more than you are.

721
00:32:27,666 --> 00:32:30,250
My right shoulder's dislocated.

722
00:32:31,166 --> 00:32:34,458
- It's--it's my fault.

723
00:32:34,875 --> 00:32:36,833
So I have to take
responsibility.

724
00:32:36,916 --> 00:32:40,416
If I don't, I can't do anything
for Sister.

725
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:42,291
For you, either.

726
00:32:42,708 --> 00:32:44,291
- [grunts]
- I'm terrible,

727
00:32:44,375 --> 00:32:46,375
and I haven't changed at all.

728
00:32:46,458 --> 00:32:48,458
I committed the same sin today

729
00:32:48,541 --> 00:32:50,666
that I did when
I was a little girl.

730
00:32:51,458 --> 00:32:54,833
<i>Because I hesitated to extend</i>
<i>my hand to you...</i>

731
00:32:56,625 --> 00:32:58,333
<i>The Witch's scent?</i>

732
00:32:58,750 --> 00:33:00,291
<i>You nearly died.</i>

733
00:33:04,291 --> 00:33:05,833
- Let me get this straight.

734
00:33:05,916 --> 00:33:09,000
Are you trying to tell me that
you decided to do this alone

735
00:33:09,083 --> 00:33:10,416
to make amends for that?

736
00:33:11,583 --> 00:33:12,625
Rem...

737
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:16,458
- Yes, what?

738
00:33:16,541 --> 00:33:18,458
- Super slap!

739
00:33:20,125 --> 00:33:22,416
For starters,
are you dumb?

740
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:24,833
No, you are dumb!
- Barusu,

741
00:33:24,916 --> 00:33:26,708
the cut that's on your forehead
has reopened

742
00:33:26,791 --> 00:33:28,250
and is bleeding again.
- Yeah, I know.

743
00:33:28,333 --> 00:33:29,916
I feel it.
I'm dumb, too, okay?

744
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:32,541
Thanks for the reminder,
but your sister is even dumber!

745
00:33:32,625 --> 00:33:33,750
Listen to me for a second.

746
00:33:33,833 --> 00:33:35,583
Where I come from there's an old
saying that goes,

747
00:33:35,666 --> 00:33:36,875
"Three heads are better
than one."

748
00:33:36,958 --> 00:33:38,333
Or, wait.
Is it two heads?

749
00:33:38,416 --> 00:33:39,833
Whatever, that doesn't matter
right now.

750
00:33:39,916 --> 00:33:41,500
The point is, three heads
thinking together

751
00:33:41,583 --> 00:33:43,500
are way harder to break
than one arrow by itself.

752
00:33:43,583 --> 00:33:45,541
So don't think
about stuff alone.

753
00:33:45,625 --> 00:33:48,208
Just learn to trust and rely
on those around you.

754
00:33:48,583 --> 00:33:50,208
- Subaru, I--

755
00:33:51,208 --> 00:33:52,583
[gasps]
[[rustling]

756
00:33:54,250 --> 00:33:55,875
- Damn it.

757
00:33:56,250 --> 00:33:58,708
