00:36:20,083 --> 00:36:21,083
Crap!

826
00:36:21,166 --> 00:36:26,541
[groaning]

827
00:36:26,625 --> 00:36:29,250
Think it's about time
for you to die!

828
00:36:29,333 --> 00:36:32,833
[roaring]

829
00:36:32,916 --> 00:36:34,666
What's the matter, mutt?

830
00:36:34,750 --> 00:36:36,500
Bring it on,
big boss Garm!

831
00:36:36,583 --> 00:36:38,083
[snarls]

832
00:36:38,166 --> 00:36:39,791
<i>- Ulgoa!</i>

833
00:36:47,583 --> 00:36:49,000
Oh, my!

834
00:36:49,083 --> 00:36:52,958
You look an absolute fright,
don't you, Subaru?

835
00:36:53,041 --> 00:36:54,916
- [groans]

836
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,666
Better late than never, I guess.

837
00:36:56,750 --> 00:36:58,041
Right, Ros?

838
00:36:58,125 --> 00:36:59,625
- [chuckles]

839
00:36:59,708 --> 00:37:01,250
- [shudders]

840
00:37:01,333 --> 00:37:03,583
Gotta say, though,
I'm surprised you knew

841
00:37:03,666 --> 00:37:04,833
where to find me.

842
00:37:04,916 --> 00:37:07,958
- Miss Emilia drove it into me
quite thoroughly

843
00:37:08,041 --> 00:37:09,458
in the village.
- [gasps]

844
00:37:09,541 --> 00:37:10,916
- "Even if it's rash
or reckless,

845
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,291
"he'll use magic
if he's cornered,

846
00:37:12,375 --> 00:37:14,916
so don't lose sight of him
from above," she said.

847
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,416
And there you go.

848
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:18,541
- Lord Roswaal!
[both grunting]

849
00:37:18,625 --> 00:37:22,708
- [breathing heavily]

850
00:37:22,791 --> 00:37:24,708
I'm certain we caused a lot
of trouble for you.

851
00:37:24,791 --> 00:37:26,000
My apologies.

852
00:37:26,083 --> 00:37:28,166
- Quite the contrary.

853
00:37:28,250 --> 00:37:30,458
Truthfully, you both
accomplished fine work

854
00:37:30,541 --> 00:37:32,208
in my absence.
I'm grateful.

855
00:37:34,208 --> 00:37:36,333
And I will certainly
show that gratitude

856
00:37:36,416 --> 00:37:38,083
for what you've done for me.

857
00:37:38,166 --> 00:37:39,666
You have my word.

858
00:37:40,833 --> 00:37:42,250
- Subaru!
- [grunts]

859
00:37:42,333 --> 00:37:45,000
Rem, that hurts!
Stop it!

860
00:37:45,083 --> 00:37:47,625
I kinda hurt all over right now.

861
00:37:47,708 --> 00:37:50,500
- You're alive!
You stayed alive!

862
00:37:50,583 --> 00:37:53,708
Subaru, I'm so happy
you're safe!

863
00:37:53,791 --> 00:37:55,458
- This again, huh?

864
00:37:55,541 --> 00:37:57,791
Suppose I should be used to it.

865
00:38:04,083 --> 00:38:05,458
[groans]

866
00:38:06,416 --> 00:38:10,375
[birds chirping]

867
00:38:10,458 --> 00:38:12,416
- Hey, are you awake?

868
00:38:12,500 --> 00:38:15,458
<i>[soft guitar music]</i>

869
00:38:15,541 --> 00:38:18,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

870
00:38:18,541 --> 00:38:19,916
- [grunts]

871
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:22,541
Was I the one who did this?

872
00:38:22,625 --> 00:38:24,708
I grabbed you and never let go?

873
00:38:24,791 --> 00:38:27,583
- Uh, well, not exactly.
