like you were in pain

876
00:38:33,125 --> 00:38:35,791
while you slept so I...

877
00:38:35,875 --> 00:38:37,750
- You held my hand?

878
00:38:38,458 --> 00:38:40,541
- I don't know what to do
at times like these.

879
00:38:40,625 --> 00:38:43,041
It's always so confusing
and overwhelming.

880
00:38:43,125 --> 00:38:45,458
So I did what would have
made me the happiest

881
00:38:45,541 --> 00:38:46,875
if I were in your place.

882
00:38:46,958 --> 00:38:48,708
- I'd like to hear the rest
of that.

883
00:38:48,791 --> 00:38:52,583
I mean, I'd like to find out
how everything ended.

884
00:38:52,666 --> 00:38:54,541
Like, were my curses removed?

885
00:38:54,625 --> 00:38:55,875
- They were.

886
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:58,250
Lord Roswaal was meticulous
and took care of all

887
00:38:58,333 --> 00:39:00,208
the mabeasts in the forest.

888
00:39:00,291 --> 00:39:01,750
So there's no chance the curses

889
00:39:01,833 --> 00:39:03,541
placed on you
will ever activate.

890
00:39:03,625 --> 00:39:05,083
- Oh.

891
00:39:07,750 --> 00:39:09,875
- I'm so sorry, Subaru.

892
00:39:09,958 --> 00:39:12,708
- Hey, come on.
Lift your head up, Rem.

893
00:39:12,791 --> 00:39:15,000
There's nothing wrong with me.

894
00:39:16,875 --> 00:39:19,875
You know, you always look
so calm and collected.

895
00:39:19,958 --> 00:39:22,916
But you're not either
of those things at all, are you?

896
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:25,458
- I'm aware of my shortcomings.

897
00:39:25,916 --> 00:39:27,250
At the heart of it all,

898
00:39:27,333 --> 00:39:30,458
I'm a powerless and incompetent
demon clan drop-out.

899
00:39:30,541 --> 00:39:33,958
So no matter what I do,
I can never match my sister.

900
00:39:34,041 --> 00:39:35,791
I'm only her replacement.

901
00:39:35,875 --> 00:39:38,375
One far inferior to her,
at that.

902
00:39:38,458 --> 00:39:39,791
Good for nothing.

903
00:39:44,166 --> 00:39:45,666
I don't get it.

904
00:39:45,750 --> 00:39:49,166
Why was I the only one
between us that kept her horn?

905
00:39:49,708 --> 00:39:51,541
Why couldn't it have been her?

906
00:39:51,625 --> 00:39:54,458
Why couldn't Sister be the one
to keep hers?

907
00:39:54,541 --> 00:39:56,458
Why was she born
with only one horn?

908
00:39:56,541 --> 00:39:58,291
I've caused her nothing
but trouble

909
00:39:58,375 --> 00:39:59,583
since the day of our birth.

910
00:39:59,666 --> 00:40:01,375
It's my fault.

911
00:40:01,458 --> 00:40:04,208
Why did we have to come into
this world as twins?

912
00:40:04,291 --> 00:40:05,750
- [grunts]

913
00:40:05,833 --> 00:40:07,833
- [gasps]
Goodness, I'm sorry.

914
00:40:07,916 --> 00:40:10,416
That was a strange thing
for me to say.

915
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:11,958
Please forgive it.

916
00:40:12,541 --> 00:40:13,541
- [grunts]

917
00:40:14,166 --> 00:40:15,791
You know, Rem,

918
00:40:15,875 --> 00:40:17,250
you keep putting Ram
on a pedestal

919
00:40:17,333 --> 00:40:19,791
while undermining yourself
at the same time.

920
00:40:19,875 --> 00:40:21,708
Putting yourself down.

921
00:40:21,791 --> 00:40:23,916
But I don't think her situation
would be any better

922
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,750
if she were in your position.

923
00:40:26,250 --> 00:40:28,791
Ram is weaker than you.
She can't cook.

924
00:40:28,875 --> 00:40:30,208
She slacks off on the job.

925
00:40:30,291 --> 00:40:31,541
She says mean things.

926
00:40:31,625 --> 00:40:33,166
- Y--you're wrong!

927
00:40:33,250 --> 00:40:35,083
If she had her horn,

928
00:40:35,166 --> 00:40:37,166
you wouldn't say things
like that.

929
00:40:38,083 --> 00:40:41,250
- But Ram doesn't have her horn,
so I don't know that Ram.

930
00:40:41,333 --> 00:40:43,208
I've never seen her
any other way.

931
00:40:44,250 --> 00:40:45,541
To be perfectly honest,

932
00:40:45,625 --> 00:40:47,583
I'm pretty sure you're
the only one who cares whether

933
00:40:47,666 --> 00:40:49,166
she has one or not.

934
00:40:49,250 --> 00:40:50,333
- [gasps]

935
00:40:50,416 --> 00:40:53,291
- And what Ram doesn't have,
you do.

936
00:40:53,375 --> 00:40:55,583
You should just acknowledge
and accept that.

937
00:40:56,166 --> 00:40:57,791
You're kind,
hardworking,

938
00:40:57,875 --> 00:40:59,750
and you always do your best
no matter what.

939
00:40:59,833 --> 00:41:02,208
Your chest is even bigger
than hers, too.

940
00:41:02,291 --> 00:41:03,375
- [grunts]

941
00:41:03,458 --> 00:41:05,958
- But seriously,
if you hadn't been around,

942
00:41:06,041 --> 00:41:07,833
those dogs would have
chewed me to death.

943
00:41:08,958 --> 00:41:11,625
I was saved because
you were there.

944
00:41:11,708 --> 00:41:14,083
As you can see,
I'm alive right now.

945
00:41:14,166 --> 00:41:16,333
Not only because
of everything Ram did...

946
00:41:17,541 --> 00:41:18,791
But because of you.

947
00:41:21,541 --> 00:41:24,458
- My true sister could have done
so much more back there.

948
00:41:25,208 --> 00:41:28,375
- You may be right,
but the one who was there for me

949
00:41:28,458 --> 00:41:31,333
was you.
- [gasps]

950
00:41:31,416 --> 00:41:33,791
- I'm glad you were there.

951
00:41:33,875 --> 00:41:35,750
Thanks for saving me.

952
00:41:36,916 --> 00:41:38,375
- Didn't you hear?

953
00:41:38,458 --> 00:41:40,625
I told you that I'm only
my sister's replacement.

954
00:41:40,708 --> 00:41:41,875
Nothing more.

955
00:41:41,958 --> 00:41:43,833
- Don't define yourself
that way, all right?

956
00:41:43,916 --> 00:41:45,083
It's too sad.

957
00:41:45,166 --> 00:41:46,875
'Course, I haven't actually
heard the details

958
00:41:46,958 --> 00:41:48,791
about how she lost her horn
in the first place,

959
00:41:48,875 --> 00:41:51,000
and I won't ask,
so I'll never know.

960
00:41:51,083 --> 00:41:52,916
Since I don't, that means
I get to talk

961
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,875
as if I know all about it.

962
00:41:56,666 --> 00:41:58,083
Listen carefully.

963
00:41:58,166 --> 00:42:01,166
All you have to do is be
the horn Ram doesn't have.

964
00:42:01,916 --> 00:42:04,583
If you do that,
you two can be a demon together.

965
00:42:04,666 --> 00:42:06,375
- [whimpers]

966
00:42:06,458 --> 00:42:09,125
- Also, you call yourself
a replacement,

967
00:42:09,208 --> 00:42:11,541
but no one could
ever take your place.

968
00:42:12,625 --> 00:42:13,791
- But I--

969
00:42:13,875 --> 00:42:15,916
- Where I come from,
there's an old saying.

970
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:18,750
"Demons laugh when you talk
about next year."

971
00:42:18,833 --> 00:42:20,250
And you're a demon.

972
00:42:20,333 --> 00:42:23,000
So just laugh, Rem.

973
00:42:23,083 --> 00:42:26,458
Wipe off that sad face
and laugh.

974
00:42:26,541 --> 00:42:29,333
Laugh while we talk
about the future.

975
00:42:30,208 --> 00:42:32,375
<i>Let's talk about things</i>
<i>while we look forward</i>

976
00:42:32,458 --> 00:42:36,125
<i>to making up for all the time</i>
<i>you've wasted by looking back.</i>

977
00:42:36,208 --> 00:42:38,666
<i>We can start by talking</i>
<i>about tomorrow.</i>

978
00:42:38,750 --> 00:42:40,583
<i>- Wait, tomorrow?</i>

979
00:42:40,666 --> 00:42:42,750
<i>- Yep, absolutely.</i>

980
00:42:42,833 --> 00:42:44,625
<i>You can say anything.</i>

981
00:42:44,708 --> 00:42:48,041
<i>Like, uh, whether you'll make</i>
<i>a Japanese,</i>

982
00:42:48,125 --> 00:42:50,416
<i>western, or local style</i>
<i>breakfast tomorrow.</i>

983
00:42:51,041 --> 00:42:53,625
<i>Or whether you'll put on your</i>
<i>right or left shoe first.</i>

984
00:42:53,708 --> 00:42:56,083
<i>It can be something</i>
<i>silly like that.</i>

985
00:42:56,166 --> 00:42:57,958
<i>No matter how it might sound,</i>

986
00:42:58,041 --> 00:43:01,166
<i>you can talk about tomorrow</i>
<i>because you have a tomorrow.</i>

987
00:43:01,250 --> 00:43:02,416
<i>How about it?</i>

988
00:43:03,333 --> 00:43:04,958
- Listen.

989
00:43:05,041 --> 00:43:06,750
I've been very weak.

990
00:43:07,166 --> 00:43:10,750
So I'm certain that I'll end up
depending and leaning on you.

991
00:43:10,833 --> 00:43:12,625
- What's wrong with that?

992
00:43:12,708 --> 00:43:15,250
- I may be weak, stupid,
and scary-looking,

993
00:43:15,333 --> 00:43:17,708
and as I'm sure you've noticed,
I'm pretty dense.

994
00:43:17,791 --> 00:43:19,291
But I never let that stop me.

995
00:43:19,375 --> 00:43:21,791
I still live my life expecting
others to take care of things

996
00:43:21,875 --> 00:43:23,625
for me when I can't handle it.

997
00:43:23,708 --> 00:43:26,375
We can just lean on each other
as we move forward.

998
00:43:27,083 --> 00:43:28,250
- [gasps]

999
00:43:28,333 --> 00:43:30,000
- Let's laugh and talk
about tomorrow

1000
00:43:30,083 --> 00:43:32,666
with our arms around each
other's shoulders.

1001
00:43:32,750 --> 00:43:35,166
After all, I've dreamed
of laughing and talking

1002
00:43:35,250 --> 00:43:37,791
about next year with a demon
since I can remember.

1003
00:43:39,541 --> 00:43:40,500
- [gasps]

1004
00:43:40,583 --> 00:43:42,750
You are demonically inspired.

1005
00:43:42,833 --> 00:43:44,916
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1006
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:46,250
- You know it.

1007
00:43:46,916 --> 00:43:50,291
- [crying]

1008
00:44:09,458 --> 00:44:10,916
- By the way, Ram,

