00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:12,208
did you happen to find the one

1010
00:44:12,291 --> 00:44:15,291
who was controlling
the mabeasts?

1011
00:44:15,375 --> 00:44:16,625
- Yes.

1012
00:44:16,708 --> 00:44:18,833
But the trail
has already vanished.

1013
00:44:18,916 --> 00:44:21,875
One of the children Barusu
and Rem brought back

1014
00:44:21,958 --> 00:44:24,791
from the forest mysteriously
disappeared from the village

1015
00:44:24,875 --> 00:44:27,000
the next day.
- Was this connected

1016
00:44:27,083 --> 00:44:28,708
to the battle
for the throne as well?

1017
00:44:28,791 --> 00:44:31,125
The Bowel Hunter,
mabeast masters,

1018
00:44:31,208 --> 00:44:33,916
we've certainly gotten involved
with some bizarre characters,

1019
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:35,791
haven't we?
- No matter how many strange

1020
00:44:35,875 --> 00:44:37,166
characters you face,

1021
00:44:37,250 --> 00:44:39,041
you aren't the sort of man
who would lose heart

1022
00:44:39,125 --> 00:44:41,125
and turn tail, are you?
- My goodness.

1023
00:44:41,208 --> 00:44:43,250
You've grown so very audacious.

1024
00:44:44,541 --> 00:44:45,625
Come here.

1025
00:44:49,583 --> 00:44:50,583
Now then.

1026
00:44:50,666 --> 00:44:52,375
Shall we begin?

1027
00:44:52,458 --> 00:44:54,500
After all, I was unable
to attend for you

1028
00:44:54,583 --> 00:44:55,791
for a whole night.

1029
00:44:55,875 --> 00:44:58,000
- Yes, I realize that.
I'm sorry.

1030
00:44:58,083 --> 00:44:59,375
Please do.

1031
00:44:59,458 --> 00:45:01,666
- You've used quite
a lot of mana.

1032
00:45:02,625 --> 00:45:04,333
May the stars protect you.

1033
00:45:08,166 --> 00:45:09,833
- [sighs]

1034
00:45:10,250 --> 00:45:12,625
- I will be busy again
for a time.

1035
00:45:12,708 --> 00:45:14,625
I know it will be difficult
for you.

1036
00:45:14,708 --> 00:45:17,250
But I'll be counting
on you and Rem.

1037
00:45:17,333 --> 00:45:18,625
- As you wish.

1038
00:45:19,791 --> 00:45:21,291
Since that fiery night,

1039
00:45:21,375 --> 00:45:24,375
my body has belonged to you,
Lord Roswaal.

1040
00:45:24,458 --> 00:45:26,125
- This battle for the throne,

1041
00:45:26,208 --> 00:45:29,291
I must win no matter what
it takes to do so.

1042
00:45:29,375 --> 00:45:31,250
For the sake
of my ultimate goal.

1043
00:45:31,333 --> 00:45:32,708
- [gasps]

1044
00:45:33,916 --> 00:45:37,416
- For the coming day
when I kill the dragon.

1045
00:45:38,916 --> 00:45:40,291
- I've noticed something.

1046
00:45:40,375 --> 00:45:42,625
You're constantly getting hurt,
aren't you, Subaru?

1047
00:45:42,708 --> 00:45:44,708
You came to this mansion because
you were injured

1048
00:45:44,791 --> 00:45:45,958
in the first place.

1049
00:45:46,041 --> 00:45:48,291
And it's only been
four days since then.

1050
00:45:49,041 --> 00:45:50,375
- Hey, give me a break.

1051
00:45:50,458 --> 00:45:52,000
It's not like I get hurt
because I want to.

1052
00:45:52,083 --> 00:45:53,916
The world's a pretty
harsh place.

1053
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,041
But I think it's a little
harsher on me.

1054
00:45:56,125 --> 00:45:57,375
With that in mind,

1055
00:45:57,458 --> 00:45:58,666
you're welcome
to spoil me rotten

1056
00:45:58,750 --> 00:46:00,916
since no one else will, Mili.
What do you say?

1057
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:02,458
- Don't joke around.

1058
00:46:02,541 --> 00:46:05,000
Puck kept trying to stop me
from leaving the cottage

1059
00:46:05,083 --> 00:46:06,791
and going after you guys
to help, too.

1060
00:46:06,875 --> 00:46:08,166
Who know what would
have happened

1061
00:46:08,250 --> 00:46:09,833
if Roswaal hadn't made it back?

1062
00:46:09,916 --> 00:46:11,333
You understand now?

1063
00:46:11,416 --> 00:46:12,750
- [grunts]

1064
00:46:13,500 --> 00:46:16,250
- Still, I suppose
you saved me again.

1065
00:46:16,333 --> 00:46:17,208
- Huh?

1066
00:46:17,291 --> 00:46:18,625
- I brought you to the mansion

1067
00:46:18,708 --> 00:46:19,833
as thanks for rescuing me

1068
00:46:19,916 --> 00:46:21,666
and you've gone
and repeated that favor

1069
00:46:21,750 --> 00:46:23,416
without a second thought.

1070
00:46:23,500 --> 00:46:26,083
So I just wanted
to say thank you.

1071
00:46:26,666 --> 00:46:27,583
- [gasps]

1072
00:46:27,666 --> 00:46:29,166
Hey, it's fine, really.

1073
00:46:29,250 --> 00:46:30,583
I only did it 'cause
I wanted to.

1074
00:46:30,666 --> 00:46:31,791
There's no thanks needed.

1075
00:46:31,875 --> 00:46:33,166
- I thought you might say that.

1076
00:46:33,250 --> 00:46:35,000
But I don't feel any better
about you

1077
00:46:35,083 --> 00:46:36,458
putting yourself in danger.

1078
00:46:36,541 --> 00:46:38,708
I should do something
to show my gratitude.

1079
00:46:38,791 --> 00:46:39,833
- I see.

1080
00:46:39,916 --> 00:46:42,083
Well, I'll take you up on that.

1081
00:46:42,750 --> 00:46:45,541
By having you go on a date
with me, Mili!

1082
00:46:45,625 --> 00:46:47,041
- And what is a date?

1083
00:46:47,125 --> 00:46:49,375
- We'll go out together,
see the same things,

1084
00:46:49,458 --> 00:46:51,208
eat the same things,
do the same things,

1085
00:46:51,291 --> 00:46:52,458
and share the same memories.

1086
00:46:52,541 --> 00:46:54,625
We'll spend our time just
laughing and having fun.

1087
00:46:54,708 --> 00:46:57,125
- And that's really
all you want?

1088
00:46:57,208 --> 00:46:58,541
- That's exactly what I want.

1089
00:46:58,625 --> 00:47:01,083
I want to show you off to those
bratty village kids

1090
00:47:01,166 --> 00:47:03,500
and there's this awesome flower
field to walk through, too.

1091
00:47:03,583 --> 00:47:06,000
Even if all we do is stroll
around and look at stuff.

1092
00:47:06,083 --> 00:47:08,208
It'll be a special occasion
for me.

1093
00:47:10,583 --> 00:47:11,583
- [sighs]

1094
00:47:11,666 --> 00:47:13,208
All right, then.

1095
00:47:13,291 --> 00:47:14,916
I'll go on a date with you.

1096
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:16,416
It sounds like fun.

1097
00:47:17,708 --> 00:47:19,333
- [shudders]

1098
00:47:19,750 --> 00:47:23,291
Yes!
That's why you're my EMF!

1099
00:47:23,375 --> 00:47:25,041
Oh, that's just a cool acronym.

1100
00:47:25,125 --> 00:47:27,583
EMF stands for Emilia Major
Faerie!

1101
